name: Stuffed Bell Peppers
description: A healthy, flavorful and wholesome nut-free meal perfect for dinner
ingredients:
4 large bell peppers
1 cup cooked quinoa
1 can (14 oz) black beans, drained and rinsed
1 cup corn kernels
1/2 cup diced tomatoes
1/4 cup chopped cilantro
1 teaspoon cumin
1 teaspoon chili powder
1/2 teaspoon garlic powder
Salt and pepper to taste
1 cup shredded cheese (optional)
instructions:
Preheat the oven to 375°F (190°C).
Cut the tops off the bell peppers and remove the seeds and membranes.
In a large bowl, combine the cooked quinoa, black beans, corn, diced tomatoes, cilantro, cumin, chili powder, garlic powder, salt, and pepper.
Divide the filling among the bell peppers. Top with shredded cheese if desired.
Place the stuffed bell peppers in a baking dish. Cover with foil and bake for 25-30 minutes.
Remove the foil and bake for an additional 5-10 minutes, or until the cheese is melted and bubbly. Serve hot.

Carbohydrates: 40-50 grams
Fiber: 10-15 grams

Saturated Fat: 1-2 grams

name: Hearty Beef Spaghetti Bolognese
description: Nothing more conforming than a bowl of meaty bol.
ingredients:
1 pound ground beef
1 onion, chopped
2 cloves garlic, minced
1 carrot, diced
1 celery stalk, diced
1 can (14 oz) diced tomatoes
1 can (6 oz) tomato paste
1 cup beef broth
1 teaspoon dried oregano
1 teaspoon dried basil
1/2 teaspoon red pepper flakes
Salt and pepper to taste
8 oz spaghetti
Fresh parsley for garnish (optional)
instructions:
In a large pot, cook the ground beef over medium heat until browned. Drain excess fat.
Add the chopped onion, garlic, carrot, and celery to the pot. Cook until softened, about 5-7 minutes.
Stir in the diced tomatoes, tomato paste, beef broth, oregano, basil, red pepper flakes, salt, and pepper. Bring the mixture to a simmer.
Reduce heat to low and let the sauce simmer for 30-45 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cook the spaghetti according to package instructions. Drain.
Serve the spaghetti with the Bolognese sauce. Garnish with fresh parsley if desired.

name: Chicken Curry
description: Spicy chicken curry with rice.
ingredients:
2 tablespoons vegetable oil
 1 onion, finely chopped
2 garlic cloves, minced
1-inch piece of ginger, minced
1-2 green chilies, chopped (adjust to taste)
1 pound (450g) boneless chicken thighs or breasts, cut into bite-sized pieces
1 can (14 oz) coconut milk
2 tablespoons curry powder (or to taste)
1 teaspoon ground cumin
1 teaspoon turmeric
1 teaspoon garam masala
Salt to taste
Fresh cilantro for garnish (optional)
instructions:
In a large pan, heat the vegetable oil over medium heat.
Add the chopped onion and sauté until translucent, about 5 minutes. Add the minced garlic, ginger, and green chilies, and cook for another 2-3 minutes.
Add the chicken pieces to the pan. Cook until browned on all sides, about 5-7 minutes.
Stir in the curry powder, cumin, turmeric, and salt. Cook for 1-2 minutes until fragrant.
Pour in the coconut milk, stirring to combine. Bring the mixture to a simmer.
Reduce heat to low and cover. Let it simmer for 20-25 minutes, until the chicken is cooked through and tender.
Stir in garam masala and adjust seasoning if necessary. Garnish with fresh cilantro.
Serve hot with rice or naan.

name: Vegan Burger
description: Delicious vegan burger with plant-based patty.
ingredients:
1 can (15 oz) black beans, drained and rinsed
1/2 cup cooked quinoa
1/2 cup breadcrumbs
1/4 cup chopped onion
1/4 cup chopped bell pepper
1/4 cup chopped mushrooms
1/4 cup chopped fresh parsley
1 teaspoon garlic powder
1 teaspoon onion powder
1 teaspoon smoked paprika
1/2 teaspoon salt
1/4 teaspoon black pepper
1 tablespoon olive oil
4 burger buns
Lettuce, tomato, and other toppings of choice
instructions:
In a large bowl, mash the black beans with a fork or potato masher.
Add the quinoa, breadcrumbs, onion, bell pepper, mushrooms, parsley, garlic powder, onion powder, smoked paprika, salt, and pepper. Mix until well combined.
Divide the mixture into 4 equal portions. Shape each portion into a patty.
Heat the olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat. Add the patties and cook until browned on both sides, about 4-5 minutes per side.
Toast the burger buns. Place a patty on the bottom half of each bun. Top with lettuce, tomato, and other toppings of choice. Cover with the top half of the bun.
Serve hot with fries or a side salad.

name: Beef Stew
description: Hearty beef stew with potatoes and carrots.
ingredients:
2 pounds beef chuck, cut into 1-inch cubes
Salt and pepper to taste
2 tablespoons olive oil
1 onion, chopped
2 cloves garlic, minced
2 tablespoons tomato paste
1 cup red wine
4 cups beef broth
2 bay leaves
1 teaspoon dried thyme
1 teaspoon dried rosemary
4 carrots, peeled and cut into 1-inch pieces
4 potatoes, peeled and cut into 1-inch pieces
1/2 cup frozen peas
Fresh parsley for garnish (optional)
instructions:
Season the beef cubes with salt and pepper.
In a large Dutch oven, heat the olive oil over medium-high heat. Add the beef cubes and brown on all sides. Remove the beef and set aside.
Add the chopped onion to the pot and sauté until softened, about 5 minutes. Add the minced garlic and cook for another minute.
Stir in the tomato paste and cook for 1-2 minutes. Pour in the red wine and scrape up any browned bits from the bottom of the pot.
Return the beef to the pot. Add the beef broth, bay leaves, thyme, and rosemary. Bring the mixture to a simmer, then reduce heat to low. Cover and let the stew simmer for 1 hour.
Add the carrots and potatoes to the pot. Cover and simmer for another 45 minutes, or until the vegetables are tender.
Stir in the frozen peas and cook for another 5 minutes. Adjust seasoning as needed.
Remove the bay leaves and garnish with fresh parsley. Serve hot.

Remove the pizza from the oven and let it cool slightly. Sprinkle with red pepper flakes if desired. Slice and serve hot.

name: Lentil Soup
description: This comforting dish is filling and packed with nutrients, without any nuts.
ingredients:
1 cup dried lentils
1 onion, chopped
2 carrots, chopped
2 celery stalks, chopped
2 cloves garlic, minced
1 teaspoon cumin
1 teaspoon paprika
1/2 teaspoon turmeric
1/2 teaspoon coriander

4 cups vegetable broth
1 can (14 oz) diced tomatoes
Salt and pepper to taste
Fresh parsley for garnish (optional)
instructions:

In a separate pot, heat some oil over medium heat. Add the chopped onion, carrots, and celery. Cook until softened, about 5-7 minutes. Add the minced garlic and cook for another minute.
Stir in the cumin, paprika, turmeric, coriander, and cayenne pepper. Cook for 1-2 minutes until fragrant.
Add the cooked lentils, vegetable broth, and diced tomatoes to the pot. Season with salt and pepper. Bring the mixture to a simmer.
Reduce heat to low and let the soup simmer for 20-30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Garnish with fresh parsley and serve hot.

1 tablespoon fresh thyme, chopped
1 tablespoon fresh rosemary, chopped
Salt and pepper to taste
instructions:
In a bowl, mix together the olive oil, garlic, lemon juice, lemon zest, thyme, rosemary, salt, and pepper. Add the chicken breasts and marinate for at least 30 minutes.
Preheat the grill to medium-high heat. Grill the chicken breasts for 6-7 minutes per side, or until cooked through.
Serve hot with a side of fresh vegetables or salad.

name: Rice and Peas
description: A classic carribean dish made with coconut milk, kidney beans, and aromatic spices.
ingredients:
1 cup long-grain white rice
1 can (14 oz) coconut milk
1 can (14 oz) kidney beans, drained and rinsed
1 onion, chopped
2 cloves garlic, minced
1 teaspoon thyme
1 teaspoon allspice
instructions:
In a large pot, combine the rice, coconut milk, kidney beans, onion, garlic, thyme, and allspice. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat to low, cover, and simmer for 20-25 minutes, or until the rice is cooked and the liquid is absorbed.
Serve hot as a side dish or main course.

name: Vegan Pad Thai
description: A delicious vegan version of the classic Thai noodle dish made with rice noodles, tofu, and vegetables.
ingredients:
8 oz rice noodles
1/4 cup soy sauce
2 tablespoons maple syrup
1 tablespoon rice vinegar
1 tablespoon lime juice
instructions:
Cook the rice noodles according to package instructions. Drain and set aside.
In a bowl, whisk together the soy sauce, maple syrup, rice vinegar, and lime juice.
In a large skillet, sauté the tofu until browned and crispy.
Add the vegetables to the skillet and cook until tender.
Add the cooked noodles and sauce to the skillet. Toss to combine.
Garnish with chopped peanuts, cilantro, and lime wedges before serving.

name: Plantain Chips
description: Crispy and flavorful plantain chips made with ripe plantains and spices.
ingredients:
2 ripe plantains
2 tablespoons olive oil
1 teaspoon paprika
1/2 teaspoon garlic powder
1/2 teaspoon onion powder
Salt and pepper to taste
instructions:
Preheat the oven to 400°F (200°C).
Peel the plantains and slice them thinly.
In a bowl, mix together the olive oil, paprika, garlic powder, onion powder, salt, and pepper. Toss the plantain slices in the spice mixture until coated.
Place the plantain slices on a baking sheet in a single layer. Bake for 20-25 minutes, flipping halfway through, or until crispy and golden brown.
Serve the plantain chips hot as a snack or side dish.

name: Vegetable Stir Fry
description: A quick and healthy mix of colorful vegetables in a savory sauce.
ingredients:
2 tablespoons vegetable oil
1 onion, sliced
2 cloves garlic, minced
1 bell pepper, sliced
1 zucchini, sliced
1 cup broccoli florets
1 cup snap peas
1/4 cup soy sauce
1 tablespoon rice vinegar
1 tablespoon maple syrup
1 teaspoon sesame oil
1 tablespoon cornstarch
1/4 cup water
instructions:
In a large skillet or wok, heat the vegetable oil over medium-high heat. Add the onion and garlic and cook until fragrant.
Add the bell pepper, zucchini, broccoli, and snap peas to the skillet. Cook until the vegetables are tender-crisp.
In a bowl, whisk together the soy sauce, rice vinegar, maple syrup, sesame oil, cornstarch, and water.
Pour the sauce over the vegetables and toss to coat. Cook until the sauce thickens.
Serve hot over rice or noodles.
